  This is a monolithic Streamlit application with a single
  1,573-line app.py file serving as an academic research dashboard.
  While functionally effective, it shows classic signs of organic
  growth from prototype to production.

  ğŸ¯ Key Architectural Patterns

  Current Architecture:

  - Pattern: Monolithic Single-Page Application
  - Data Flow: Linear pipeline (Load â†’ Process â†’ Cache â†’ Display)
  - State Management: Streamlit session state + file-based caching
  - Processing: Function-based with mixed concerns

  Strengths:

  - âœ… Effective Caching: Smart use of @st.cache_data across 8
  functions
  - âœ… Graceful Degradation: Fallbacks when Gensim/NLTK unavailable
  - âœ… Performance Optimization: Chunking (100k records) and
  sampling (10k)
  - âœ… Rich User Experience: Comprehensive visualizations and
  educational content

  Critical Weaknesses:

  - âŒ Monolithic Structure: All functionality in single file
  - âŒ Mixed Concerns: UI logic intertwined with business logic
  - âŒ Memory Constraints: 4.1GB datasets loaded entirely into RAM
  - âŒ No Modularity: Tight coupling between components

  ğŸ“Š Data Architecture Assessment

  Processing Pipeline:

  CSV Files â†’ load_datasets() â†’ preprocess_data_full() â†’ Pickle 
  Cache â†’ Analysis â†’ UI

  Strengths:
  - Vectorized pandas operations for threat detection
  - Pre-compiled regex patterns for performance
  - Intelligent sampling for expensive NLP operations

  Weaknesses:
  - No data validation or schema enforcement
  - Missing data lineage tracking
  - No streaming for large datasets

